  "translations": {
    "en": "While the Commander of the Faithful (peace be upon him) was addressing the people, saying: \"Ask me before you lose me, for by God, there is nothing from the past nor anything of the future that you ask me about except that I shall inform you of it.\" Then Sa'd ibn Abu Waqqas stood up before him and said: \"O Commander of the Faithful, tell me how many hairs are on my head and in my beard.\" He said to him: \"Verily, by God, you have asked me about a matter regarding which my friend, the Messenger of God (may God bless him and his family) had told me that you would ask. There is not a single hair on your head or in your beard except that at its root sits a devil. And indeed in your house there is an infant who shall kill al-Husayn, my son.\" And Umar ibn Sa'd was at that time a toddler, crawling on his hands.",
